The Kenya Volleyball Federation Nairobi branch tournament that was set for March 4-5  at the Nairobi University grounds will now be played at Eastleigh high school instead. The UON venue is fully booked for other sports events according to information on KVF's social media pages. This will be the first event of the year in volleyball to be hosted by the  Nairobi branch. Moses Mbuthia who is in charge of beach volleyball is the main sponsor for the two-day tournament. Other sponsors will be unveiled before the championship. Primary schools willing to be involved will part with Sh1,000 as a fee. Secondary schools will pay a mandatory Sh1,500 while Universities and colleges will be charged Sh2,000. Teams plying trade in the national league will cough Sh3,000 as self-supporting clubs will pay Sh1,500.